Open Material Transfer Agreement (OpenMTA)

Copyright (c) 2026 OpenCyclo Initiative Contributors

The biological protocols, standard operating procedures (SOPs), strain
information, and wetware documentation contained in this repository are
shared under the terms of the Open Material Transfer Agreement (OpenMTA).

The OpenMTA is a unified, standardized material transfer agreement designed
to enable the free sharing of biological materials and associated knowledge
for research, education, and humanitarian purposes.

Full agreement text: https://www.addgene.org/open-mta/

Key Principles:
- Materials and associated knowledge are shared openly.
- Recipients may use, modify, and redistribute materials and protocols.
- Attribution to the original creators is required.
- No restrictions on field of use for research and non-profit purposes.

The OpenCyclo Initiative wetware protocols are designed for operators without
advanced microbiology degrees, following OpenMTA compliance guidelines.
